   Who's News:
   BEI Holdings Ltd.
   Restructures Managers
</HL>
<DATE>
04/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS BEIH
</CO>
<LP>
   ATLANTA -- BEI Holdings Ltd. said it completed a top
management restructuring following last year's acquisition of
Golembe Associates Inc., and consolidated its East Coast and
West Coast consulting operations.
   The financial institution consulting company named Nevins
D. Baxter to the new position of vice chairman of BEI
Holdings. Mr. Baxter, 48 years old, was formerly chairman of
Golembe Associates.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Thomas M. McGrath has been named to the new post of
chairman and chief executive officer of BEI Golembe
Consulting, the company's primary consulting subsidiary. Mr.
McGrath, 41, was previously president of the company's West
Coast consulting operation.
   Peter Merrill has been named president of BEI Golembe
Consulting, also a new position. The 54-year-old Mr. Merrill
will take on national responsibility for sales and
implementation of consulting services, and business
development.
