<HL>
   China's Industrial Output
</HL>
<DATE>
04/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<LP>
   BEIJING -- China' slumping economy recorded zero growth in
industrial output during the first quarter, although some
signs of recovery were seen in March.
   State Statistical Bureau figures, reported in the Chinese
official press, also showed that smaller township and private
enterprises continued to expand, while state-run enterprises
showed declining output and productivity.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Industrial output for March was up 1.4% from the like
month in 1989. Output in state enterprises was the same as
last year, while collectives showed 0.7% growth, township
enterprises 5.4% and others, mainly small private firms,
32.3%.
</TEXT>
