   OSLO -- Norway's consumer prices rose 1.1% in March from
February and were up 4.5% from a year earlier, the Central
Bureau of Statistics announced.
   The new index figure was 229.8 as of March 15, up from
227.2 Feb. 15 and up from 219.8 as of March 15, 1989 (1979
equals 100).
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Contributing most to last month's increase was the index
group for clothes and shoes, which rose 4.9% from the
previous month, the bureau said.
